 the taken-for-granted assumptions which underpin current interpretations and presents an original and revisionist account of Benin art history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aBini (African people)xReligious life and customs. 0aRites and ceremonieszNigeriazBenin City. 0aShrineszNigeriazBenin City. 4aAfrican Studies. 7aHISTORY / Africa / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z97831107804680 cprintz978074863316640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781474468589?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474468589423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474468589/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK